<TITLE> Arrest terrorists, corrupt before polls: Badruddoza </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 26 (bdnews24.com)  Bikalpadhara Bangladesh president AQM Badruddoza Chowdhury on Friday asked authorities to arrest terrorists and corrupt people before the general elections. He was speaking at a function at Photo Journalists Association auditorium in the city where more than 50 activists led by former chief engineer of the Public Works Department Mohammad Yusuf joined the party at the function. He welcomed those who joined his party and said, "You are joining a new type of politics. This party is with the people and will always fight against corruption and terrorism." The former president demanded completion of the trial of the corruption suspects before the election. "They must be punished. Against whom no allegation will be proved will have to be released with honour." "The government took power pledging to eliminate corruption and terrorism but could not fulfil all its pledges." On joining electoral alliance, he said, "His party will not join any alliance that has been involved in corruption and plundering, and ruined the country." Bikalpadhara secretary general retired major Abdul Mannan, Dr Nurul Amin Bepari, principal Abdur Rashid, Abdur Rahim, Morshed Rashed and Prof Anwara Begum were present. bd
